bill_title: Congratulating the town of Tyndall on its 125th anniversary celebration of its founding.

bill_versions.bill_text: A LEGISLATIVE COMMEMORATION, Congratulating the town of Tyndall on its 125th anniversary celebration of its founding. WHEREAS, Tyndall was surveyed and platted by D.W. Currier in 1879. The town was located at the junction of the Running Water and Charles Mix county branch of the Chicago, Milwaukee, and St. Paul Railroad Company. The first building in town was the railway depot; and WHEREAS, Tyndall is located near the geographical center of Bon Homme County, became the county seat in the spring of 1885, and was incorporated in 1887; and WHEREAS, Tyndall will be celebrating its first one hundred and twenty-five years of growth and progress on June 26 and 27 in the year 2004: NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT COMMEMORATED, by the Seventy-ninth Legislature of the State of South Dakota, that the town of Tyndall be honored on the occasion of its 125th anniversary celebration of its founding.
